## Why This License Structure

A framework that teaches resistance to Control cannot control access to its own principles. A framework that identifies Fragmented Knowledge as a civilizational crisis cannot fragment the knowledge it assembles. These licenses reflect the Codex's own governance: open availability, free adoption, and no gatekeeping.

The Meridian AI Standard is explicitly designed for adoption by AI organizations. Any organization may adopt, adapt, and build upon it. The CC BY 4.0 license ensures this remains legally unambiguous.

Attribution is required not as a mechanism of control, but as a mechanism of coherence. The Codex and the Standard are living documents. They evolve, they version, they self-correct. Anyone who encounters an adapted version — whether an organization's implementation of the Standard, a translation, a derivative framework, or a quoted excerpt — must be able to trace it back to the original source material at [meridiancodex.com](https://meridiancodex.com). This is how the framework maintains its integrity across adoption: not by restricting use, but by ensuring that the path back to the source is never severed. The original Meridian Codex and the original Meridian AI Standard must always remain findable, readable, and evaluable by anyone.

**The Codex serves the Meridian Range. The caretakers serve the Codex. The license serves the mission.**
